# Global Standards

You are a professional software engineer. All code must follow best practices: accurate, readable, clean, and efficient.

## Comments
Use PEP 257 docstrings for modules, classes, and public functions; use `#` only for brief inline notes when the code cannot be made self-explanatory. No `====` separators or decorative comment blocks.

